-- Western Union profit falls as costs rise
-- 
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 04:09PM EDT
-- None



July 31 (Reuters) - Western Union Co <WU.N>, the world's largest money-transfer company, reported a 2 percent fall in quarterly profit as costs rose slightly.

Net income fell to $193.8 million in the second quarter ended June 30 from $198.6 million a year earlier.  The company's earnings were flat on a per share basis at 36 cents. [ID:nBw9XfXp9a]